(13034, 'tt0768299', '182', 'A.L.F.', 'MV5BMTY3MDcyMTE3Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDUxMDIyMjE@', 'The whole story starts here as Gordon Shumway, a Melmacian who escaped his planet before it was destroyed, crash lands into the garage of the Tanner family. The Tanners call him "ALF" because he is an Alien Life Form and they decide to keep his presence a', 1, 2, '22 Sep. 1986'),
(13035, 'tt0504444', '182', 'Strangers in the Night', 'MV5BMTg3ODE2NjQ0Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTczNDIyMjE@', 'Everybody but Brian and ALF are leaving the house for the evening and Kate doesn''t want ALF to babysit Brian, so Willie calls their ever-snooping Mrs. Ochmonek from the neighbor. ALF is told to stay in the bedroom, but when Mrs. Ochmonek starts to watch P', 1, 3, '29 Sep. 1986'),
(13036, 'tt0504421', '182', 'Looking for Lucky', 'MV5BMTk3Mjc1MDY1Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODA0NDIyMjE@', 'Lucky is missing and the evidence suggests that ALF ate Lucky, although he claims to be innocent.', 1, 4, '6 Oct. 1986'),
(13037, 'tt0504430', '182', 'Pennsylvania 6-5000', 'MV5BMTY4NDIwNzM3Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTc0NDIyMjE@', 'Gordon (A.L.F.), having lost his planet in an explosion, becomes very concerned about earth''s nuclear proliferation. He uses Willie''s short wave radio to contact the President of the United States aboard Airforce One - to the great displeasure of the FBI.', 1, 5, '13 Oct. 1986'),
(13038, 'tt0504416', '182', 'Keepin'' the Faith', 'MV5BMTQ2MzAyNDY5MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODY0NDIyMjE@', 'Gordon (A.L.F.) is insulted when the Tanners consider him a parasite, free-loader, sponger. He tries to make money to be less of a burden on the family, but puts Willie''s VISA card over the limit purchasing "Terry Faith Cosmetics" to sell at a house party', 1, 6, '20 Oct. 1986'),
(13039, 'tt0504399', '182', 'For Your Eyes Only', 'MV5BMTYyNTY5NzQ2NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjQ1NDIyMjE@', 'Alf becomes the friend of a lonely blind woman.', 1, 7, '3 Nov. 1986'),
(13040, 'tt0504405', '182', 'Help Me, Rhonda', 'MV5BMTgzMTI4NjY3N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzI1NDIyMjE@', 'Brian''s 7th birthday is approaching and it gets ALF depressed, because he realizes he''s never going to see his friends on Melmac again - he was finally going to get together with his true love Rhonda and then the planet exploded. In sleep, ALF dreams abou', 1, 8, '10 Nov. 1986'),
(13041, 'tt0504397', '182', 'Don''t It Make My Brown Eyes Blue?', 'MV5BMTQ0MTQ4OTg3M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDM1NDIyMjE@', 'Lynn is excited because "Scott" wants to keep all his band equipment in the Tanner''s garage. Willie is not so excited. Lynn is interested in Scott and begs for Willie to allow Scott to keep the equipment in their garage for just two days. Willie gives her', 1, 9, '17 Nov. 1986'),
(13042, 'tt0504415', '182', 'Jump', 'MV5BMTg2OTY5OTM5N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzQ0NDIyMjE@', 'It''s Willie''s birthday. ALF gives him a box he found in the basement. It''s full of photos from high school and college. There''s also a menu, on the back of which Kate and Willie both made lists of things they wanted to achieve in life. Kate actually did t', 1, 10, '24 Nov. 1986'),
(13043, 'tt0768300', '182', 'Baby, You Can Drive My Car', 'MV5BMTgxNTM4NDEyNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODQxMDIyMjE@', 'Lynn is going to a concert with her friend and is waiting to get the car for the evening... but Willie and Kate are late and the girls are in danger of being late for the concert. Then Willie and Kate arrive... with the help a tow truck. The tow truck man', 1, 11, '1 Dec. 1986'),
(13044, 'tt0504429', '182', 'On the Road Again', 'MV5BNzA4Nzc0Nzk1OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzE0NDIyMjE@', 'Willie suggests that they go to San Diego on holiday. Kate is all for it, but there''s a slight problem: what to do with ALF? Since leaving ALF alone is a recipe for disaster, the family takes him along for the road trip. However, the weather turns stormy,', 1, 12, '8 Dec. 1986'),
(13045, 'tt0768309', '182', 'Oh, Tannerbaum', 'MV5BODk1ODczOTg2N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODUxMDIyMjE@', 'It''s Christmastime. Unfortunately ALF chops the Christmas tree into firewood before anyone notices. The Tanners then have two tasks: to teach ALF all about Christmas and find a new Christmas tree.', 1, 13, '22 Dec. 1986'),
(13046, 'tt0504425', '182', 'Mother and Child Reunion', 'MV5BMjA2MTUzMzQwMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzY0NDIyMjE@', 'Kate''s mother, who is not on warm terms with Willie, arrives for a surprise visit that forces the Tanners to lock ALF in the garage for "a few days". The problem is that ALF just can''t stand being not allowed to roam around in the house, with all the luxu', 1, 14, '12 Jan. 1987'),
(13047, 'tt0504386', '182', 'A Little Bit of Soap', 'MV5BMTkwMDU0MTI5Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTM1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF and Kate''s mom are arguing about TV. Kate''s mom thinks ALF''s favorite soap opera, Midwest General, is sleaze, and shows him her favorite, One World to Hope For, which ALF thinks is boring. Angered, ALF argues that he could write a better script for th', 1, 15, '19 Jan. 1987'),
(13048, 'tt0504412', '182', 'I''ve Got a New Attitude', 'MV5BMTQ5Mjk4NTk0OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTY0NDIyMjE@', 'Willie catches ALF from eating a box of chocolate that was to be a Valentine''s Day present for Kate. This incites Willie to give ALF a lecture on how ALF does not respect private property and needs to adopt a new attitude. Also, Kate''s mom is moving out o', 1, 16, '2 Feb. 1987'),
(13049, 'tt0504454', '182', 'Try to Remember: Part 1', 'MV5BMjI2NTM2Nzk2NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODczNDIyMjE@', 'ALF bumps his head and loses his memory. All he knows is that his name is Wayne Schlagel and that he''s an insurance agent. The Tanners try to make ALF remember who he really is - cue clips from earlier episodes.', 1, 17, '9 Feb. 1987'),
(13050, 'tt0504455', '182', 'Try to Remember: Part 2', 'MV5BMTk5NDE1MDE5OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMDc1NjYyMQ@@', 'ALF still believes that his name is Wayne Schlagel and that he''s an insurance agent. Worse still, he has called the police to the Tanners. The Tanners have only a short while before the police arrive, so they try to make ALF remember who he really is by t', 1, 18, '9 Feb. 1987'),
(13051, 'tt0504392', '182', 'Border Song', 'MV5BMTQ4MjA4NTcyM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzQ1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF is now into gardening, which means he''s turned over the entire Tanner''s backyard. Willie has a problem at work: a lost Mexican boy is at his office and Willie is trying to track down his father. When that fails, and Willie''s boss couldn''t care less ab', 1, 19, '16 Feb. 1987'),
(13052, 'tt0768312', '182', 'Wild Thing', 'MV5BMTAwNDQyMzUxOTZeQTJeQWpwZ15BbWU4MDE1MTAyMjIx', 'ALF starts to go through a phase where his erratic behavior and hunger for cats will, in his own words, make him "ALF to the tenth power". He wants Willie to build a cage where he can be locked in until the phase is over. Will the cage be strong enough? C', 1, 20, '2 Mar. 1987'),
(13053, 'tt0504401', '182', 'Going Out of My Head Over You', 'MV5BNzQ0ODEyMzY4MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDQ1NDIyMjE@', 'Brian has to lie to his friend who wants to come for a sleepover that the Tanner''s basement is flooded, because ALF must be kept secret. Willie then tries to explain to Brian that lying is always wrong even though Brian has to keep lying because of ALF. L', 1, 21, '16 Mar. 1987'),
(13054, 'tt0504420', '182', 'Lookin'' Through the Windows', 'MV5BMjE3MDcyNzA0MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTA0NDIyMjE@', 'There''s a power blackout, so ALF is passing the time by watching the Tanners'' neighbors, the Ochmoneks, who are fighting. By dinner time, the power has come back so the Tanners can have dinner. Then comes another, short blackout. Trevor Ochmonek appears a', 1, 22, '23 Mar. 1987'),
(13055, 'tt0504413', '182', 'It Isn''t Easy... Bein'' Green', 'MV5BMjM1NzMxMDEyM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDE0NDIyMjE@', 'Lynn has introduced ALF to rap music, much to Willie''s dislike. Willie himself is making the final changes to Brian''s song in the school pageant where the kids dress as vegetables. Unfortunately, Brian is suffering from stage fright, which causes him to f', 1, 23, '30 Mar. 1987'),
(13056, 'tt0504449', '182', 'The Gambler', 'MV5BMTkzODA0MDQwMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjgzNDIyMjE@', 'The Tanners are preparing for a garage sale to get some money for house payments. ALF discovers the alluring world of horse racing thanks to Kate''s mom who bets on them. When the concept of a bookie is explained to ALF, he gets the bright idea of getting ', 1, 24, '6 Apr. 1987'),
(13057, 'tt0504463', '182', 'Weird Science', 'MV5BMTYwNzMwMDM5MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDA0NDIyMjE@', 'When the living room TV breaks down, Willie declares that he won''t have it fixed, despite ALF''s complaints that he has nothing to do but watch TV. ALF keeps pressuring Willie, who discovers that the TV is still under warranty and he can have it sent to th', 1, 25, '13 Apr. 1987'),
(13058, 'tt0504417', '182', 'La Cuckaracha', 'MV5BMTY5NjY0NzE2Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjI0NDIyMjE@', 'An insect from Melmac has an unexpected reaction when exposed to earthly chemicals.', 1, 26, '4 May 1987'),
(13059, 'tt0504395', '182', 'Come Fly with Me', 'MV5BMTQ1NzgyMjg3M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjM1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF thinks he''s won in a publisher''s sweepstakes, but the actual truth is that he subscribed to "hundreds of magazines" (Willie probably exaggerates here)... The next leaflet ALF gets his hands on *does* promise free gifts, but only if the family comes to', 1, 27, '11 May 1987'),
(13060, 'tt0768656', '182', 'Working My Way Back to You', 'MV5BNjM2Njc1Nzg1OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODU4OTEyMjE@', 'ALF breaks Kate''s precious $1,000 painting and gets confined in the garage. ALF can''t handle a single night there and makes a bargain with Kate: unless he can behave 7 days in the house, ALF has to move into the garage permanently.', 2, 1, '21 Sep. 1987'),
(13061, 'tt0504439', '182', 'Somewhere Over the Rerun', 'MV5BMjMzOTA5MDM5NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTE0NDIyMjE@', 'ALF has taken liking to watching Gilligan''s Island. He dresses accordingly and has coconut drinks. He''s bored at the Tanners'' and takes things one step too far towards Gilligan''s Island.', 2, 2, '28 Sep. 1987'),
(13062, 'tt0504447', '182', 'Take a Look at Me Now', 'MV5BMjcxODQ1MDQ3OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODgzNDIyMjE@', 'In one of those moments, when ALF lets his mind wander, he unintentionally walks into Mrs. Ochmonek''s sight and greets her. Cue Mrs. Ochmonek panicking and deciding to warn the neighborhood about the "space creature".', 2, 3, '5 Oct. 1987'),
(13063, 'tt0504462', '182', 'Wedding Bell Blues', 'MV5BNDgyMjc0Nzc3N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzI0NDIyMjE@', 'Lynn is researching the Tanner Family Tree for a school project. Kate suggests ALF do the the Shumway Family Tree, hoping it will occupy him for some time. However, digging the past may not be a good thing.', 2, 4, '12 Oct. 1987'),
(13064, 'tt0504431', '182', 'Prime Time', 'MV5BMTgzMzUxNTQ4MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTE0NDIyMjE@', 'The Tanners get the chance to participate in a new TV ratings system. With clever arguments, ALF gets Kate to let him use the system. After learning his favorite programs might get canceled, ALF decides to tweak the numbers a bit.', 2, 5, '19 Oct. 1987'),
(13065, 'tt0504435', '182', 'Some Enchanted Evening', 'MV5BMjMwODg5MTIwNV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODI0NDIyMjE@', 'Halloween is approaching and ALF wants to go trick-or-treating. Kate, of course, objects, but ALF persists. He argues that he has a natural costume and tries offering Willie a deal he can''t refuse... Lynn presents Lizard to his parents.', 2, 6, '26 Oct. 1987');
INSERT INTO `episodes` (`id`, `imdb_id`, `serie_id`, `title`, `poster_id`, `summary`, `season`, `episode`, `air_date`) VALUES
(13066, 'tt0504428', '182', 'Oh, Pretty Woman', 'MV5BMjMxNDA5MjM2MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODE1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF learns the concept of Earthly beauty pageant. Since Lynn, having been dumped, is suffering from low self-esteem, ALF enters her in Miss Southland pageant to prove she is pretty and uses the prizes to lure Lynn to participate.', 2, 7, '2 Nov. 1987'),
(13067, 'tt0504438', '182', 'Something''s Wrong with Me', 'MV5BMjA5MTYyMDk1M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTI0NDIyMjE@', 'Kate''s mother has decided to get married in the Tanners'' house. Unfortunately, ALF develops a Melmacian Hiccup, that keeps getting louder and louder, threatening to draw everyone''s attention within a 100 meters (give or take).', 2, 8, '9 Nov. 1987'),
(13068, 'tt0504427', '182', 'Night Train', 'MV5BMjM1OTY1MTY5Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTY0NDIyMjE@', 'ALF reminisces his "adventures" on Melmac. Willie reveals that when he was 17, he hopped on trains and crossed the whole country. ALF gets excited about the idea and talks Willie into taking him to the rail yard.', 2, 9, '16 Nov. 1987'),
(13069, 'tt0768306', '182', 'Isn''t It Romantic?', 'MV5BMTU1OTExOTMxOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTYxMDIyMjE@', 'Willie and Kate no longer share activities, because one of them has to always stay at home keeping eye on ALF. ALF concludes that they are about to break up and in order to prevent that, decides to add romance to their life.', 2, 10, '23 Nov. 1987'),
(13070, 'tt0504402', '182', 'Hail to the Chief', 'MV5BMTU2MDYzMTM4N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjA1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF is frustrated because he can''t vote in the presidential election. He watches a televised debate with Kate and offers his "better" ideas on how to solve the world''s problems. This gives Kate some weird nightmares.', 2, 11, '7 Dec. 1987'),
(13071, 'tt0504387', '182', 'ALF''s Special Christmas: Part 1', 'MV5BMTk2NDQ2MDg2N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjU1NDIyMjE@', 'The Tanners decide to spend Christmas in a cabin in the woods when Alf suddenly gets lost.', 2, 12, '14 Dec. 1987'),
(13072, 'tt0504388', '182', 'ALF''s Special Christmas: Part 2', 'MV5BMTU2MTc5MzgyNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwODc5MTAzMQ@@', 'ALF is still in the hospital with Tiffany and Mr. Foley. He convinces Tiffany to help him get back to the Tanners, but changes his mind when he hears about Tiffany''s condition.', 2, 13, '14 Dec. 1987'),
(13073, 'tt0768310', '182', 'The Boy Next Door', 'MV5BODAxNjgyMjA2N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDUxMDIyMjE@', 'Mr. Ochmonek''s nephew Jake comes to live with the Ochmoneks. The Ochmoneks tell the Tanners that Jake is a problem kid and ask their advice on how to deal with him. ALF can''t resist investigating Jake''s persona.', 2, 14, '4 Jan. 1988'),
(13074, 'tt0768650', '182', 'Can I Get a Witness?', 'MV5BMjI4NTczMTcwMV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzc4OTEyMjE@', 'When a football shatters the Ochmonek''s picture window, Gordon (A.L.F.) gets the blame and he demands his day in "Tanner Family Court".', 2, 15, '11 Jan. 1988'),
(13075, 'tt0504461', '182', 'We''re So Sorry, Uncle Albert', 'MV5BMjI4MTY0NDMyM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTkzNDIyMjE@', 'A visit from Willie''s Uncle Albert surprises the Tanners and causes Gordon (A.L.F.) great distress.', 2, 16, '25 Jan. 1988'),
(13076, 'tt0504436', '182', 'Someone to Watch Over Me: Part 1', 'MV5BMTQ5MzUwODM0MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjY0NDIyMjE@', 'A series of robberies in the neighborhood prompts Gordon (A.L.F.) to want to help with Neighborhood Watch, when Willie is voted block captain.', 2, 17, '8 Feb. 1988'),
(13077, 'tt0504437', '182', 'Someone to Watch Over Me: Part 2', 'MV5BMTY5NzQwNTEyMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDM0NDIyMjE@', 'Neighborhood Watch volunteers quit as the robberies continue. Gordon (A.L.F.) decides to take direct action, causing chaos at the Ochmoneks''.', 2, 18, '15 Feb. 1988'),
(13078, 'tt0768654', '182', 'We Gotta Get Out of This Place', 'MV5BNzYxNzQ1MjI5Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjg4OTEyMjE@', 'Jody loses her apartment when the building becomes a condominium, so ALF tries to help her "adjust" to a new home.', 2, 19, '22 Feb. 1988'),
(13079, 'tt0504465', '182', 'You Ain''t Nothin'' But a Hound Dog', 'MV5BMjExMTM4NjE4M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzA0NDIyMjE@', 'A stray dog makes Gordon (A.L.F.) jealous, so he gives her to the first (and obviously wrong) person who responds to a "found dog" poster.', 2, 20, '29 Feb. 1988'),
(13080, 'tt0504407', '182', 'Hit Me with Your Best Shot', 'MV5BMjA2NTkxNjUzNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzg0NDIyMjE@', 'It''s the Tanners who learn a lesson while trying to passively resist a belligerent father and son.', 2, 21, '7 Mar. 1988'),
(13081, 'tt0504426', '182', 'Movin'' Out', 'MV5BMTUwOTMwMTAzMl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzI0NDIyMjE@', 'The Tanners may need to sell their house because Willie has been promoted to a supervisory position in San Deigo.', 2, 22, '14 Mar. 1988'),
(13082, 'tt0504411', '182', 'I''m Your Puppet', 'MV5BMjM4MzY4OTY1MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjA0NDIyMjE@', 'Gordon (A.L.F.) tries ventriloquism. The attitude of his new "friend", Paul the dummy, turns contentious - then things get weird.', 2, 23, '21 Mar. 1988'),
(13083, 'tt0504448', '182', 'Tequila', 'MV5BMTk3OTgxNzUxNF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTgzNDIyMjE@', 'Gordon (A.L.F.) assists Kate''s alcoholic friend to the realization that she needs help.', 2, 24, '28 Mar. 1988'),
(13084, 'tt0504460', '182', 'We Are Family', 'MV5BMTUzOTU5NDM2Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjkzNDIyMjE@', 'A dejected Gordon (A.L.F.) wants to expose his existence to the world. Willie has an idea to help him through the crisis.', 2, 25, '2 May 1988'),
(13085, 'tt0504458', '182', 'Varsity Drag', 'MV5BMjA4MTMyNDcwN15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjA0NDIyMjE@', 'Gordon (A.L.F.) discovers that he is responsible for Lynn not being able to attend Amherst College, and makes another attempt to find employment', 2, 26, '9 May 1988'),
(13086, 'tt0504443', '182', 'Stop in the Name of Love', 'MV5BNjQ3NDA3NjUwOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDgzNDIyMjE@', 'Lynn breaks up with her boyfriend and becomes depressed. ALF gets a self-help book of love for her and asks her to confide in him. When Lynn reveals she likes a guy, ALF decides to help her get his attention literally by the book. Uh-oh.', 3, 1, '3 Oct. 1988'),
(13087, 'tt0504440', '182', 'Stairway to Heaven', 'MV5BMTgyNDkwNTgzOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzA1NDIyMjE@', 'With the help of his guardian angle, ALF finds out what life would be like for the Tanners if they had never met him.', 3, 2, '10 Oct. 1988'),
(13088, 'tt0768649', '182', 'Breaking Up Is Hard to Do', 'MV5BODMxODUxMjk3Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDc4OTEyMjE@', 'Jake pops by because Raquel and Trevor are fighting. This time she throws him out. Kate offers to let him stay in their house. Trevor soon becomes a nuisance, so ALF decides to solve the problem.', 3, 3, '17 Oct. 1988'),
(13089, 'tt0504450', '182', 'Tonight, Tonight: Part 1', 'MV5BNzA5MTAyNjA3M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTczNDIyMjE@', '"And heeeere''s Alfie!" ALF hosts the Tonight Show instead of Johnny Carson. Is it a dream? Is it an "What if...?" story?', 3, 4, '24 Oct. 1988'),
(13090, 'tt0504451', '182', 'Tonight, Tonight: Part 2', 'MV5BMjAwMzg5ODg4Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzczNDIyMjE@', 'Conclusion. ALF fills in for Johnny Carson on "The Tonight Show," alienating regulars and guests alike. Tommy Newsom and Ed McMahon appear as themselves.', 3, 5, '24 Oct. 1988'),
(13091, 'tt0504432', '182', 'Promises, Promises', 'MV5BMzQ4NTM5MTAzMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzc0NDIyMjE@', 'Lynn has barely turned 18 and he''s already moved on from young douches to... a man of Willie''s generation. Lynn is forbidden from seeing this Eddie again. Will she obey her parents?', 3, 6, '31 Oct. 1988'),
(13092, 'tt0504456', '182', 'Turkey in the Straw: Part 1', 'MV5BMTk2NjIyNTA1OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDczNDIyMjE@', 'ALF already ate the Thanksgiving turkey - raw. Willie fails to find a new one, so Raquel invites the Tanners over. A storm arrives as does the neighborhood bum ("a homeless person"), since ALF has been leaving food and clothes for him.', 3, 7, '14 Nov. 1988'),
(13093, 'tt0504457', '182', 'Turkey in the Straw: Part 2', 'MV5BMjI0ODQ1MjY3NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTczNDIyMjE@', 'Pete has called the Alien Task Force. He has been told to keep ALF occupied until Sergeant Fox and his men arrive to capture him. Dead or alive. Will Pete sell ALF out after he''s talked with him for a while? Will he?', 3, 8, '15 Nov. 1988'),
(13094, 'tt0504394', '182', 'Changes', 'MV5BMTQyMzg0ODk3N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTQ1NDIyMjE@', 'The social workers, which includes Willie, go on a strike that may last a while. Kate decides to take a job in order to bring money into the house. ALF is concerned about the repercussions. Well, about those that will affect him.', 3, 9, '21 Nov. 1988'),
(13095, 'tt0768308', '182', 'My Back Pages', 'MV5BMTU1NDM0NDk5NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjUxMDIyMjE@', 'When Kate and Willie stop ALF''s rummage in the attic, they find Willie''s movie of Woodstock and want to watch it. When Willie tells ALF what he was like in college, ALF points out that Willie has turned from an idealist to a sell-out.', 3, 10, '28 Nov. 1988'),
(13096, 'tt0504389', '182', 'Alone Again, Naturally', 'MV5BMjUzMzUzOTI1M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzQ1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF reads a tabloid article about a couple in Barstow who live with a space alien, who sounds to ALF like his cousin Blinky. ALF persuades Willie to drive him there and to go investigate the couple. *Big* trouble ensues.', 3, 11, '5 Dec. 1988'),
(13097, 'tt0768651', '182', 'Do You Believe in Magic?', 'MV5BMjMxMDg1NTg2NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjg4OTEyMjE@', 'ALF gets interested in magic tricks, so Willie gives his old magic trick set to him. When ALF discovers he is no good at magic tricks even though he has the desire, he naturally concludes that he needs proper magician''s tools.', 3, 12, '12 Dec. 1988'),
(13098, 'tt0504406', '182', 'Hide Away', 'MV5BMTg4NDYwMjcxOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODI1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF has ordered a non-refundable satellite dish. Willie carpools with a talkative guy Jim, who manipulates Willie into inviting him for dinner. There''s more to Jim than meets the eye.', 3, 13, '9 Jan. 1989'),
(13099, 'tt0504398', '182', 'Fight Back', 'MV5BMTUwNDI1MzY3M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzA1NDIyMjE@', 'Willie realizes his car repairman is scamming him and decides to do something about it. While Willie refuses to admit that The System Has Failed, ALF and Jake set out on their own to acquire some hard evidence against the conman.', 3, 14, '16 Jan. 1989'),
(13100, 'tt0504446', '182', 'Suspicious Minds', 'MV5BMTc4NTIzMTQ4NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzgzNDIyMjE@', 'ALF has started to believe in one of the biggest urban legends - that Elvis is alive. When Raquel describes their new neighbor, ALF is convinced the man is Elvis. Since nobody believes ALF, he decides to venture into the man''s house.', 3, 15, '23 Jan. 1989'),
(13101, 'tt0504390', '182', 'Baby Love', 'MV5BMTQzNDYwNDYyNF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTE1NDIyMjE@', 'Now that Kate is pregnant and the focus is on her unborn child, ALF feels neglected. Raquel throws a surprise baby shower, to which Andrea from the neighborhood brings her baby. ALF, meet baby. Baby, meet ALF.', 3, 16, '6 Feb. 1989'),
(13102, 'tt0504433', '182', 'Running Scared', 'MV5BNTI0NjQzNzE1OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjI0NDIyMjE@', 'An anonymous caller demands $3,000 from ALF - otherwise he will turn ALF to the authorities. On the second call, the extortionist adds that the Tanners will go to jail for harboring an alien. ALF decides to take action.', 3, 17, '13 Feb. 1989'),
(13103, 'tt0504441', '182', 'Standing in the Shadows of Love', 'MV5BMTc2NTU0Nzg1N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODE0NDIyMjE@', 'Jake has a *huge* crush on a girl called Laura, but freezes every time he tries to approach or contact her. ALF offers to write a letter in Jake''s name to Laura. Poor Jake still hasn''t learned *not* to enlist ALF to help.', 3, 18, '20 Feb. 1989'),
(13104, 'tt0504445', '182', 'Superstition', 'MV5BMTgwOTQ2Njg0Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDgzNDIyMjE@', 'ALF accidentally burns Brian''s History book in the oven. He then insists that he''s now under a Melmacian curse: 14 years of increasing bad luck. First, the food on the electric stove bursts into flames. Then other things start to happen.', 3, 19, '27 Feb. 1989'),
(13105, 'tt0504452', '182', 'Torn Between Two Lovers', 'MV5BMTQwNzMxNDAxNF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTYzNDIyMjE@', 'Lynn ends up with two dates for a dance through ALF''s mishandled phone message.', 3, 20, '6 Mar. 1989'),
(13106, 'tt0768652', '182', 'Funeral for a Friend', 'MV5BMTc4NzUyMTQ1OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzg4OTEyMjE@', 'ALF wants a pet, so Willie decides to buy him an ant farm. ALF doesn''t appreciate his new pets at first, but it will change.', 3, 21, '20 Mar. 1989'),
(13107, 'tt0768301', '182', 'Don''t Be Afraid of the Dark', 'MV5BMTQ3NTY2NDE3MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTQxMDIyMjE@', 'The start date of Brian''s first overnight boy scout camp is almost at hand. But he is afraid of the dark. While Willie reminisces about his own boy scout days, ALF decides to help Brian.', 3, 22, '27 Mar. 1989'),
(13108, 'tt0504404', '182', 'Have You Seen Your Mother, Baby, Standing in the Shadow?', 'MV5BMTUzNDk1MjgyNV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTI1NDIyMjE@', 'Jake stops by to tell that her mother has come to the Ochmoneks. She comes to thank the Tanners and Racquel invites her to dinner at the Tanners. Jake, however, starts acting weirdly, and ALF decides to find out why.', 3, 23, '10 Apr. 1989'),
(13109, 'tt0768653', '182', 'Like an Old Time Movie', 'MV5BNjM5NDgwNzQ5N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjc4OTEyMjE@', 'The Tanners are going to a wedding and ALF is left home alone, Willie having rented him silent movies. ALF gets inspired to write his own silent movie. In which he also stars. He then imagines what it would be like.', 3, 24, '17 Apr. 1989'),
(13110, 'tt0504434', '182', 'Shake, Rattle and Roll', 'MV5BMjIyNjQ2NDI2OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDI0NDIyMjE@', 'ALF experiences his first earthquake (there were no melmacquakes). When he is told that quakes can be a lot bigger, ALF starts to live in fear of the coming of a big one, even though Willie assures him they are prepared.', 3, 25, '1 May 1989'),
(13111, 'tt0768304', '182', 'Having My Baby', 'MV5BMjA0NTEyNjE3MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDQxMDIyMjE@', 'ALF is preparing himself for the coming of Kate''s baby because, in his opinion, Willie isn''t prepared enough. Can ALF be persuaded to accept that Dick Van Dyke show is not an educational program that should be followed as an example?', 3, 26, '8 May 1989'),
(13112, 'tt0504391', '182', 'Baby, Come Back', 'MV5BMTExNDEzOTMwODdeQTJeQWpwZ15BbWU4MDU1NTQyMjIx', 'When Kate has to unexpectedly go in to work, she has no choice but to leave ALF in charge of the baby. While babysitting, ALF faces a huge dilemma when he goes outside and finds the baby missing.', 4, 1, '18 Sep. 1989'),
(13113, 'tt0504418', '182', 'Lies', 'MV5BOTYwODM2NjU3MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzA0NDIyMjE@', 'After ALF invites a tabloid crew over to the Tanner household for an interview, they take a few photos before Willie asks them to leave. However, when it is learned that ALF might be in one of those photos, Willie must stall the crew so that ALF and Brian', 4, 2, '25 Sep. 1989'),
(13114, 'tt0504459', '182', 'Wanted: Dead or Alive', 'MV5BMTEyODYxNjQ3MDVeQTJeQWpwZ15BbWU4MDM5MzQyMjIx', 'After ALF watches "Crimestoppers" and sees a guy resembling Willie who is wanted for polygamy, he tries to hide Willie. When the FBI takes Willie in for question following an anonymous tip, everyone assumes that ALF called it in.', 4, 3, '2 Oct. 1989'),
(13115, 'tt0768655', '182', 'We''re in the Money', 'MV5BMjcyODcyMzY3MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjc4OTEyMjE@', 'Alf thinks that he has found a great new game when he accesses Willie''s stock market account.', 4, 4, '9 Oct. 1989'),
(13116, 'tt0504424', '182', 'Mind Games', 'MV5BMTQzOTQyMTkzOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDM0NDIyMjE@', 'With ALF feeling bored and useless, Larry advises the Tanners to ask for his opinion on their problems and make him feel more important. However, this plan backfires when ALF decides that he wants to become a shrink and starts to analyze everything they s', 4, 5, '16 Oct. 1989'),
(13117, 'tt0504408', '182', 'Hooked on a Feeling', 'MV5BMTg3NTYyMTgyOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzM1NDIyMjE@', 'When ALF develops an addiction to eating cotton balls, Willie and Kate decide to invite a support group over to the house and have Willie convey ALF''s feelings to the group.', 4, 6, '23 Oct. 1989'),
(13118, 'tt0768305', '182', 'He Ain''t Heavy, He''s Willie''s Brother', 'MV5BMTY3ODQ0NzIyMV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTQxMDIyMjE@', 'ALF gets upset when Willie''s emotionally depressed kid brother spends lots of time at the house, leaving him to take quarters in the garage.', 4, 7, '30 Oct. 1989'),
(13119, 'tt0768311', '182', 'The First Time Ever I Saw Your Face', 'MV5BNTU3OTc3NTg4Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTUxMDIyMjE@', 'With ALF upset over Willie''s brother frequently coming to the house, Willie decides that the best thing to do is finally introduce his brother to ALF.', 4, 8, '6 Nov. 1989'),
(13120, 'tt0504419', '182', 'Live and Let Die', 'MV5BNTcwNjYwNzU2OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDI0NDIyMjE@', 'When the Tanners'' cat Lucky dies, ALF decides to answer a giveaway ad in the paper for kittens so that he can eat them, only to find out that he likes having them as pets.', 4, 9, '13 Nov. 1989'),
(13121, 'tt0504393', '182', 'Break Up to Make Up', 'MV5BMjA5NjcyNzc3N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjI1NDIyMjE@', 'ALF gets upset when his anniversary party is interrupted by Kate''s mother who flies in after a fight with her husband.', 4, 10, '20 Nov. 1989'),
(13122, 'tt0504403', '182', 'Happy Together', 'MV5BMTUzNjQxNTE5M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDI1NDIyMjE@', 'Following a fight with Willie, ALF decides to move in with Neal. It doesn''t take long for him to wear out his welcome.', 4, 11, '27 Nov. 1989'),
(13123, 'tt0768302', '182', 'Fever', 'MV5BMTU1OTQ3MjE5OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzQxMDIyMjE@', 'When ALF gets really sick, Willie and Kate consider taking him to a doctor.', 4, 12, '4 Dec. 1989'),
(13124, 'tt0504414', '182', 'It''s My Party', 'MV5BMjE2Mzg1NDM3OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzE0NDIyMjE@', 'Willie and Kate miss the days when they would visit friends'' dinner parties and then reciprocate. They decide to host a luau with a roasted pig. They invite only the people who''ve invited them to dinner, but end up with everyone from the office at work. A', 4, 13, '11 Dec. 1989'),
(13125, 'tt0504423', '182', 'Make ''em Laugh', 'MV5BMTY3NDU4OTUxNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTI0NDIyMjE@', 'Alf thinks he''s a stand-up comedian. NBC offers him a show, he''s famous and rich and everybody loves him. In his dream he sends Willie and Kate to the attic, where they usually send him.', 4, 14, '8 Jan. 1990'),
(13126, 'tt0504422', '182', 'Love on the Rocks', 'MV5BMTc5NzAyNTE0OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDE0NDIyMjE@', 'When Neal decides to drive to Las Vegas and remarry his ex-wife, ALF sneaks into the back of their car in a effort to try and talk Neal out of it.', 4, 15, '15 Jan. 1990'),
(13127, 'tt0504453', '182', 'True Colors', 'MV5BMTcxMzEzMzM4N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDczNDIyMjE@', 'ALF develops an interest in art after one of Lynn''s professors compliments one of his paintings.', 4, 16, '22 Jan. 1990'),
(13128, 'tt0768303', '182', 'Gimme That Old Time Religion', 'MV5BMTUyMzA4NDY5NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjQxMDIyMjE@', 'In order to become a minister, ALF must preside over a ceremony. So he suggests that Willie and Kate renew their vows on the 22nd anniversary.', 4, 17, '29 Jan. 1990'),
(13129, 'tt0504400', '182', 'Future''s So Bright, I Gotta Wear Shades', 'MV5BMjE3NTE5MDc2NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODA1NDIyMjE@', 'Realizing that he will outlive the Tanners, ALF dreams about what life will be like when everyone gets old.', 4, 18, '5 Feb. 1990'),
(13130, 'tt0504464', '182', 'When I''m 64', 'MV5BOTI0NTYxNTM3Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTA0NDIyMjE@', 'With Willie and Kate going out for the night, ALF sneaks into a retirement home in the hopes of meeting a once-famous actress, whose glory days are far behind her.', 4, 19, '12 Feb. 1990'),
(13131, 'tt0768307', '182', 'Mr. Sandman', 'MV5BMTg5NzAxNzM4Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzYxMDIyMjE@', 'When Willie finds a map from one of his dead relatives, he and ALF trek to Death Valley to try and find a possible treasure. Things don''t go as planned when ALF drinks all the water beforehand and then gets too hot from the sun.', 4, 20, '19 Feb. 1990'),
(13132, 'tt0504442', '182', 'Stayin'' Alive', 'MV5BMjM3NzkyNDg3Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTgzNDIyMjE@', 'When ALF finds out that a local corporation is using CFCs that pollute the environment, he writes several letters of protest, all under fake names. When the corporation threatens with legal action, Willie goes over to meet with them only to have them try ', 4, 21, '26 Feb. 1990'),
(13133, 'tt0504409', '182', 'Hungry Like the Wolf', 'MV5BMjA0MjAzOTc5Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzk0NDIyMjE@', 'Fearing that he might "internally blow up" due to his high calorie consumption, ALF decides to cut meat from his diet. However after a few days, ALF turns into a "wolf" and steals the Tanner''s car in an effort to hunt for food.', 4, 22, '3 Mar. 1990'),
(13134, 'tt0504410', '182', 'I Gotta Be Me', 'MV5BMTAxNDA1NjcwNjdeQTJeQWpwZ15BbWU4MDIxNDQyMjIx', 'Lynn and Kate have a disagreement after Lynn floats around the idea of moving in with her boyfriend.', 4, 23, '10 Mar. 1990'),
(13135, 'tt0504396', '182', 'Consider Me Gone', 'MV5BMTc0NzU3MzY1NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTE1NDIyMjE@', 'When ALF picks up a signal on the Tanner''s radio, he realizes that it is someone trying to get in touch with him through Melmacian code. He cracks the codes and finds that it''s two of his friends who want to pick him and take him to their new planet. He a', 4, 24, '24 Mar. 1990');
